AGI - Change the law of appointment of the Rai cda, decriminalize the crime of defamation, avoid conflict of interests with the possible sale of Agi to parliamentarian Antonio Angelucci. These are the recommendations made by the MFRR consortium, Media Freedom Rapid Response>, a project funded by 2020 by the European Commission, at the end of the mission in Rome on 16 and 17 May. During a press conference at the national headquarters of the journalists' order, the seven members of the Mfrr consortium took the place of the Italian mission organized urgently and during which they met journalists, unions, institutional interlocutors and representatives of civil society.
&nbsp;
On Thursday morning the delegation took part in the sit-in that the Usigrai, the journalists' union of Rai, organized in viale Mazzini in front of the headquarters of the public TV. According to the Map on the freedom of press elaborated by the European centre for Press and Media Freedom>, Italy in the course of 2024 has already recorded 49 episodes of alert. Andreas Lamm, director of the ECPMF, reported that in the three years 2022-2024 the episodes against freedom of press in Italy were 175: it goes from physical threats, verbal intimidation, aggression, legal actions, fearful complaints and censorship. "On the public service the delegation recommends that a reform of the Renzi law be completed and we hope that it is in line with Article 5 of the European Media Freedom Act (EMFA), must be a rule aimed at allowing the appointment of members of the Board to be completely independent, and according to the same article Emfa that the financing and resources granted to the Rai may be adequate and certain. Italy will have to adapt to the Emfa by August 2025", said Sielke Kelner composed of the Media Freedom Rapid response. &nbsp;&nbsp;
<h2> The defamation
"On the defamation our recommendations are in line with international standards and in particular with the EU Anti-Sapp Directive and also with the recommendations which have been formulated by the EU - added Kelner - we urge the Italian decision maker to start a reform that provides for a full decrimination of the defamation > this archive in conjunction with a reform of the civil code, in particular We ask that a maximum compensation ceiling be set up in civil proceedings, we also wish for extra legal measures in line with the Anti Slapp recommendations, i.e. setting up some support measures such as a financial and legal support system for what are the targets of fearful actions. On the Agi case, the delegation considers that a possible transfer would constitute a conflict of interest in contrast with Article 6 of the Empha".
Question Agi</h2>
And precisely on the story involving the Italian Journalist Agency to explain the position of the consortium MFRR was Beatrice Chioccioli: "There are alarming developments for us regarding the potential acquisition of Agi by Mr Antonio Angelucci, who as you know already controls several important national newspapers. It represents a significant risk for the editorial independence of Agi> this potential sale and is in conflict with another article of the European Media Fereedom Act, Article 6 concerning editorial independence and transparency over conflicts of interest. Publishers must be free to make decisions without any interference and anyone with significant interests in media service providers must declare any conflict of interest that in this case, for us, is crystalline."
&nbsp;
< blockquote
"Our position is simple - said Beatrice Chioccioli - don't sell the Agi to Angelucci, the future of Italian democracy for us starts from a free, independent and pluralistic media panorama".
</blockquote
&nbsp;
At the meeting with the press at the headquarters of the national order of journalists Alessandra Costante, secretary of the National Federation of Press, The President Fnsi Vittorio Di Trapani, and the secretary of the National Council of the Order of Journalists, Paola Spadari.&nbsp; The members of the MFRR Commission also complained that no response from members of the majority of government to calls for comparison and dialogue was lacking.
&nbsp;
"We have forwarded a series of invitations both to representatives of the government coalition and to representatives of the oppositions, we are very sorry because in reality we have not managed to meet any of the representatives of the majority - it has emphasized Sielke Kelner - yesterday instead we have spoken with Senator Barbara Floridia, president of the committee Vigilanza Rai, with Senator Ilaria Cucchi, vice president of the justice commission to the Senate, with whom we had debated We have met and Mr Valentina Grippo of Action and Mr Pierluigi Mazzela representative of the government to the Council of Europe. Also met the representatives of the Usigrai in the sit-in of Viale Mazzini". As regards the 'electoral condicio' David Diaz - Jogeix, composed of the MFRR delegation, stressed the importance that the 'equal treatment for all candidates' is guaranteed. "Agcom - he concluded - is in line with his mandate." &nbsp;

